->Setup Instructions
1. Clone/Create Project
bash# Clone or create a new project folder
mkdir my_project
cd my_project

2. Set Up Virtual Environment
bash# Create virtual environment
python -m venv .venv
# Activate virtual environment
# Windows
.venv\Scripts\activate
# macOS/Linux
source .venv/bin/activate

3. Install Dependencies
bash# Install required packages
pip install -r requirements.txt

4.Running Jupyter Notebooks in VS Code

Open or create a .ipynb/.py file
Select kernel: .venv (Python Recommended) in the top-right corner
Run notebook cells with the play button or Shift+Enter

To run the Streamlit app, execute: streamlit run tennis_analytics_app.py

To run DB File: Use- >sqlite3 'DB file location'